		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
				<p>My Direction</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">A. Rice</persName> <placeName>133 E. Baltimore St.</placeName></p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Baltimore</placeName>&#44; <date>Monday&#44; 25 of Sivan &#40;June&#41;&#44; 1862</date>.</p>
				<p>To my friend&#44; the celebrated&#44; etc.&#44; etc. <addressee>Isaac Leeser</addressee>&#58;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Since I know very well that you&#44; my friend&#44; are ever ready to do<lb/> me a kindness&#44; therefore I come to request of you one thing which may seem<lb/> little in your eyes but to me seems very difficult.  Next week&#44; I shall<lb/> have to make a wedding speech.  The bride does not understand German<lb/> Therefore would you please be good enough to send me such a sermon<lb/> in English.  It must&#44; above all&#44; contain that the Kallah must be<lb/> a Jewish life&#44; and a hint to the wise&#44; etc.  Please write it very clear<lb/> so that I should be able to read it&#44; and send me this by <date>Friday</date> or<lb/> <date>Saturday</date>.  Since my house is too far from the synagogue&#44; I am com<lb/>pelled to change my residence next week and&#44; because of this&#44; I am<lb/> very much occupied.</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Your true friend&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">Abraham Rice</persName></p>
				<p>My direction</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">A. Rice</persName> <placeName>133 E. Baltimore St.</placeName></p>
